<h3 id="1">What is LimitBreaker?</h3>
<p>LimitBreaker is an exercise logging application that incorporates traditional role playing game mechanics. In addition to logging exercises, LimitBreaker is capable of scheduling exercises and creating routines. More features to come in the future!</p>
<a href="#" style="color:Black; font-size: 0.67em;">Top of Page</a>
<br />

<h3 id="2">How do I get started?</h3>
<p>Create an account by clicking Profile, User Routines, Workout Schedule, Log Exercises, or Exercise Goals. The functionality of these tabs will become active once you have created an account and verified your email.</p>
<a href="#" style="color:Black; font-size: 0.67em;">Top of Page</a>
<br />

<h3 id="3">How do I log an exercise?</h3>
<p>Click on the "Running" icon. Search for the exercise you wish to log via name or muscle group. Enter your stats and your performance will be tracked!</p>
<a href="#" style="color:Black; font-size: 0.67em;">Top of Page</a>
<br />

<h3 id="4">How do I create a routine?</h3>
<p>A routine is simply a collection of exercises. Click on the clipboard icon on the left and follow the simple instructions to create a routine. You can even log them in the future!</p>
<a href="#" style="color:Black; font-size: 0.67em;">Top of Page</a>
<br />

<h3 id="5">What are experience points and levels?</h3>
<p>Every time you log an exercise or routine, you will be awarded experience points. Once you have collected enough experience points, you will level up! This information is posted on our leaderboards so you can see where you rank within all LimitBreakers.</p>
<a href="#" style="color:Black; font-size: 0.67em;">Top of Page</a>
<br />

<h3 id="6">What eles can I do with LimitBreaker?</h3>
<p>You can track your weight and height change. You can also create personal goals for yourself.</p>
